<br>
Last night I went into GG mode having dinged &amp; cemented my druid. A guy was offering what I consider frankly way to much for a gg to get to a guild wedding - grats to the happy couple! I told him I'd do it free (I'm a sucker for that kind of thing), meant it, refused the trade and then he sneakily /split the pp &amp; disbanded from the group immediately so I couldn't /split it back again.  I thanked him profusely and proceeded onwards to gate several more folks about. He's on my druids friends list now = next time I won't let him be so damned sneaky!<br>
 <br>
If I'm in GG mode it usually means I'm chilling/pottering &amp; wotnot and just don't feel like doing much else.  Very few people don't say thankyou I find and a bit of a chat along the way is lovely. <br>
<br>
What goes around comes around and the ones that pay I figure cover the one's that can't. <br>
<br>
I've been in desperate need to get from a to b a few times with my main and paid for it well just asking that &quot;the next ride of a lower lvl than me goes free pls&quot;.<br>
<br>
When I get asked how much do you charge &quot;whatever&quot; really does mean just that, a thankyou, a buff, pp &quot;whatever&quot;. I wouldn't be in taxi mode if I wasn't happy to taxi damnit! And you know what - despite this I still end up looking in the inventory window and being amazed at the pp there at the end of a taxi session!<br>
 <br>
If I'm busy and not wanting to gg about I say so. All I really ask is people respect &quot;no sorry I'm exping/busy/about to log&quot;.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp's. Now chill..... or learn to say &quot;no&quot;.<br>
